'''IdeaPad'''是[[联想集团|联想集团]]面向消费者推出的[[笔记本电脑|笔记本电脑]]品牌。

== 历史 ==
IdeaPad笔记本电脑最先在2008年1月推出。<ref name="first">{{cite web |title= New from Lenovo: three IdeaPad notebook s |author= Sal Cangeloso |work= Geek.com blog |url= http://www.geek.com/articles/chips/new-from-lenovo-three-ideapad-notebooks-2008013/ |date= 2008-01-03 |accessdate= 2011-06-02 |archive-date= 2012-10-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121016050842/http://www.geek.com/articles/chips/new-from-lenovo-three-ideapad-notebooks-2008013/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>第一个产品线中的三个型号分别为Y710，Y510，U110。这些型号特点都是宽屏，支持人脸识别，无框屏幕，触摸控制，[[杜比實驗室|杜比]]扬声器系统。<ref name="first"/>

IdeaPad的设计标志着联想偏离了面向企业的ThinkPad笔记本电脑，迈向更加以消费者为导向的外观和感觉。<ref name="IdeaPad Consumer Oriented Design">{{cite web|title=Lenovo IdeaPad Hands-On Roundup|url=http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|quote=For starters, the design of the IdeaPads marks a significant change for Lenovo. Unlike the "all business" classic ThinkPad line that Lenovo inherited from IBM, the IdeaPads have a sleek, refined look with a very consumer-focused feel.|accessdate=2013-08-23|archive-date=2013-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105083135/http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|dead-url=no}}</ref>其主要体现在使用镜面屏以及不再具有传统的ThinkPad[[指点杆|指点杆]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Lenovo IdeaPad Hands-On Roundup|url=http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|quote=The glossy screens feature a flush-mount bezel which makes the transition from LCD to keyboard look incredibly smooth. Speaking of keyboards, the keyboards on both the Y510 and the Y710 have a distinctive "ThinkPad feel" when typing ... despite the loss of the iconic red trackpoint in the middle of the keyboard.|accessdate=2013-08-23|archive-date=2013-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105083135/http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|dead-url=no}}</ref>Notebook Review称其键盘有“独特的ThinkPad的感觉”和“平稳灵敏的触摸板和触摸板按钮”。<ref>{{cite web|title=Lenovo IdeaPad Hands-On Roundup|url=http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|quote=Speaking of keyboards, the keyboards on both the Y510 and the Y710 have a distinctive "ThinkPad feel" when typing ... despite the loss of the iconic red trackpoint in the middle of the keyboard. The touchpad and touchpad buttons were also smooth and responsive.|accessdate=2013-08-23|archive-date=2013-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105083135/http://www.notebookreview.com/default.asp?newsID=4188|dead-url=no}}</ref>

